<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/5846</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GWE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 11, 1 p.m. War Trade Board advises Trading with Enemy Act
                            does not apply to American nationals resident in Cuba nor to
                            partnerships composed of American nationals resident in Cuba, but does
                            apply to American corporations having mere agencies in Cuba.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>